  "text": "ROS plays an important role in LPS-induced OC formation as intracellular signaling molecules. [CITATION_1] We examined intracellular ROS levels by using the ROS Detection Kit (Beyotime Institute of Biotechnology). Flow cytometry analysis using fluorescent ROS probe revealed that LPS-mediated intracellular ROS induction was attenuated by the treatment of 15 μM EGCG or EGCG-GNPs ( Figure 5A and B). EGCGGNPs showed a more potent inhibitory effect on intracellular ROS than EGCG. These results suggested that EGCG-GNPs are better intracellular ROS scavengers than EGCG in LPSmediated osteoclastogenesis.",
